{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/64/comments/43536631.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/64/_/diff#comment-43536631"}}, "parent": {"id": 43535387, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/64/comments/43535387.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/64/_/diff#comment-43535387"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 64, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/64.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/64"}}, "title": "Fixing Windows Issues"}, "content": {"raw": "From what I understand from the CMake, it should be sufficient to just add: \n~~~cmake\ntarget_include_directories(${PROJECT_LIBRARY_TARGET_NAME} PRIVATE ${libdl_include_dir})\ntarget_link_libraries(${PROJECT_LIBRARY_TARGET_NAME} ${libdl_library})\n~~~\nI also don't understand why everything is working fine in *nix, perhaps there is some sort of transitive dependency in linking? ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>From what I understand from the CMake, it should be sufficient to just add: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-cmake\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nb\">target_include_directories</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">${</span><span class=\"nv\">PROJECT_LIBRARY_TARGET_NAME</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"s\">PRIVATE</span> <span class=\"o\">${</span><span class=\"nv\">libdl_include_dir</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">target_link_libraries</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">${</span><span class=\"nv\">PROJECT_LIBRARY_TARGET_NAME</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">${</span><span class=\"nv\">libdl_library</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>I also don't understand why everything is working fine in *nix, perhaps there is some sort of transitive dependency in linking? </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-08-24T21:20:46.286359+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Silvio Traversaro", "uuid": "{34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6/578caaa1-056c-45a2-8bf9-bee94c3bebef/128"}}, "nickname": "traversaro", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6"}, "updated_on": "2017-08-24T21:20:46.336695+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 43536631}